1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
MR. Robot Adversarial — SANS FIND EVIL! 2026
Autonomous AI cyber-defense pipeline.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:22,000
The problem: AI adversaries move in minutes.
We close the gap: scan → triage → adversarial review → verdict, ~30s.

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Three trust layers, two model families, one rule-based judge.
Scanners are deterministic; the auditor is a different model family.

4
00:00:40,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Health and quality gate: providers, scanners, audit DB.
The submitted tree passes 181 tests, with 4 skipped.

5
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Sample 1: Python bind shell. Expected verdict: MALICIOUS.
C2 URL, socket bind, and subprocess loop are visible evidence.

6
00:01:36,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Sample 2: Django view with parameterized ORM. Expected verdict: BENIGN.
Framework-aware review avoids a false alarm.

7
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Self-correction evidence from SQLite.
First verdict BENIGN → heterogeneous review → SUSPICIOUS, flipped=true, ΔA=1.0.

8
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Accuracy on 173 samples: 135 malicious + 38 benign.
Accuracy 99.42%, Precision 99.26%, Recall 100%, FPR 2.63%.

9
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:05,500
Audit trail: every decision stage writes structured evidence.
Tool, verdict, confidence, and timestamp are reconstructable.

10
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:10,500
